group to lotto... so in ordinance to the preset rules, up for grabs.  Naturally, the chanter wins, the monk pouts for a bit, but then gets over it.  Days later, the chanter - friend of mine - gets a tell from the monk that he thinks he deserves the T-Staff, and she should give it to him, and the whole loot policy was a crock to begin with.  Now, being the loot whore plat grubbing cleric that I am, I told her/him to keep it, but I know that she/he is the type of person that feels a) bad about it, or b) thinks that she/he was in the wrong from the beginning.  Any opinions would be apreciated.<br><br>Cakken out- <p><img src=http://members.home.net/tadam/caksig.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF7D6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ukabatickamikaze.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kabatic Kamikaze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#6C8361>(9/6/01 9:22:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=786.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.weezer.com/weezerfans/maillist.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Loots Lotto ~~~ T-Staff</span><hr size=1> The chanter put in the time and effort just as much as the monk did I'm sure. He/She won it, even though the loot rules were a crock, fair and square. They should keep it.. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFF8Dc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/ueinweg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>einweg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire<br><img src=http://www.winterblood.com/mmdn/star2.gif></span><br>  Pos